WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.527 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.527 --> 00:00:02.260 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, everybody.

00:00:02.260 --> 00:00:04.734 align:middle line:84%
So let's move and
look at the purpose.

00:00:04.734 --> 00:00:06.100 align:middle line:84%
The purpose of the
Awakening the Dreamer,

00:00:06.100 --> 00:00:09.350 align:middle line:84%
Changing the Dream Symposium,
which is on the screen now,

00:00:09.350 --> 00:00:12.840 align:middle line:84%
is bringing forth an
environmentally-sustainable,

00:00:12.840 --> 00:00:16.370 align:middle line:84%
spiritually-fulfilling,
socially-just human presence

00:00:16.370 --> 00:00:17.160 align:middle line:90%
on this planet.

00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:20.410 align:middle line:90%


00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.950 align:middle line:84%
And now when you look at this
and that we're committed to all

00:00:23.950 --> 00:00:26.080 align:middle line:84%
of those, it may at
first seem like these

00:00:26.080 --> 00:00:27.720 align:middle line:90%
are three separate issues.

00:00:27.720 --> 00:00:30.210 align:middle line:84%
But what I think that
you'll come to understand

00:00:30.210 --> 00:00:32.330 align:middle line:90%
is that they are not separate.

00:00:32.330 --> 00:00:35.170 align:middle line:84%
They are actually
intricately interwoven.

00:00:35.170 --> 00:00:36.860 align:middle line:90%
They're part of a whole.

00:00:36.860 --> 00:00:40.310 align:middle line:84%
And what you'll find
is that there's no way

00:00:40.310 --> 00:00:42.700 align:middle line:84%
to be able to sustain
any kind of progress

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:47.210 align:middle line:84%
if you only focus on one
and ignore the other two.

00:00:47.210 --> 00:00:49.190 align:middle line:90%
So they are very much connected.

00:00:49.190 --> 00:00:51.110 align:middle line:84%
And we know that by
the end of the day,

00:00:51.110 --> 00:00:53.850 align:middle line:84%
by the end of this symposium,
you'll be even more deeply

00:00:53.850 --> 00:00:56.650 align:middle line:90%
aware of that connection.

00:00:56.650 --> 00:00:58.640 align:middle line:84%
And I think we understand
that some of you

00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:01.970 align:middle line:84%
have been committed in
action in these areas

00:01:01.970 --> 00:01:04.220 align:middle line:84%
for a long, long time,
and we acknowledge

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:06.380 align:middle line:90%
that and thank you for that.

00:01:06.380 --> 00:01:10.470 align:middle line:84%
And in that context, maybe today
will occur as an opportunity

00:01:10.470 --> 00:01:14.260 align:middle line:84%
to deepen your understanding,
explore some new perspectives,

00:01:14.260 --> 00:01:15.820 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps expand
and strengthen

00:01:15.820 --> 00:01:18.940 align:middle line:84%
your own commitment to what
you're already engaged in.

00:01:18.940 --> 00:01:21.790 align:middle line:84%
And so how we are going
to go through these,

00:01:21.790 --> 00:01:24.950 align:middle line:84%
the flow of the symposium, is
through a series of questions.

00:01:24.950 --> 00:01:28.650 align:middle line:84%
So the first question
is, where are we?

00:01:28.650 --> 00:01:32.960 align:middle line:84%
Given that we're bringing forth
an environmentally-sustainable,

00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:36.550 align:middle line:84%
spiritually-fulfilling, and
socially-just human presence,

00:01:36.550 --> 00:01:42.290 align:middle line:84%
where are we are in relationship
to each of those areas?

00:01:42.290 --> 00:01:46.230 align:middle line:84%
And it is very important that
we have some shared knowledge

00:01:46.230 --> 00:01:47.780 align:middle line:84%
about that because that
will be a foundation

00:01:47.780 --> 00:01:49.510 align:middle line:90%
piece for our work together.

00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:53.090 align:middle line:84%
And then the second question
is, how did we get here?

00:01:53.090 --> 00:01:54.930 align:middle line:84%
So this is a very,
very important question

00:01:54.930 --> 00:01:56.810 align:middle line:84%
because rather than--
generally after we

00:01:56.810 --> 00:01:59.120 align:middle line:84%
hear where we are
in any problems,

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:02.170 align:middle line:84%
the natural instinct
is to run to fix it.

00:02:02.170 --> 00:02:03.820 align:middle line:84%
But we need to slow
down and figure

00:02:03.820 --> 00:02:05.330 align:middle line:90%
out, how did we get here?

00:02:05.330 --> 00:02:07.830 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to have a
special kind of analysis

00:02:07.830 --> 00:02:09.810 align:middle line:84%
that we'll get to be
involved in to look at,

00:02:09.810 --> 00:02:11.740 align:middle line:90%
what is the root cause?

00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:13.340 align:middle line:84%
Not just the
superficial behavior,

00:02:13.340 --> 00:02:15.570 align:middle line:84%
but what is really
underneath this, so

00:02:15.570 --> 00:02:17.960 align:middle line:90%
that we can make other choices?

00:02:17.960 --> 00:02:22.200 align:middle line:84%
And then the third question
is, what is emerging now?

00:02:22.200 --> 00:02:22.990 align:middle line:90%
What is happening?

00:02:22.990 --> 00:02:24.455 align:middle line:90%
What is possible?

00:02:24.455 --> 00:02:28.960 align:middle line:84%
Not only what is possible, what
is already emerging through us,

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:31.380 align:middle line:90%
around us, throughout the world?

00:02:31.380 --> 00:02:33.630 align:middle line:84%
And then the fourth
and final question

00:02:33.630 --> 00:02:35.770 align:middle line:90%
is, where do we go from here?

00:02:35.770 --> 00:02:38.010 align:middle line:84%
And probably this question
is the most important

00:02:38.010 --> 00:02:46.000 align:middle line:84%
of all because then we're asking
ourselves, what are you to do?

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.330 align:middle line:90%
What are you to be?

00:02:48.330 --> 00:02:52.730 align:middle line:84%
How do you fit into
what is happening?

00:02:52.730 --> 00:02:55.070 align:middle line:84%
And what are the actions
that we need to take

00:02:55.070 --> 00:02:58.510 align:middle line:90%
to create the new dream?

00:02:58.510 --> 00:03:00.890 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, so let's start
with the first question.

00:03:00.890 --> 00:03:03.160 align:middle line:84%
And the first question
is, where are we?

00:03:03.160 --> 00:03:07.850 align:middle line:84%
And we'll examine where we are
together at this moment in time

00:03:07.850 --> 00:03:11.410 align:middle line:84%
through the three lenses of
the environment, of society,

00:03:11.410 --> 00:03:14.710 align:middle line:84%
and our own personal
and spiritual concern.

00:03:14.710 --> 00:03:16.880 align:middle line:84%
This is not meant to
be new information.

00:03:16.880 --> 00:03:19.770 align:middle line:84%
I think most of us have heard
a lot of this information.

00:03:19.770 --> 00:03:21.800 align:middle line:84%
And what too often
happens, though,

00:03:21.800 --> 00:03:23.590 align:middle line:84%
if we've heard a lot
of this information,

00:03:23.590 --> 00:03:26.270 align:middle line:84%
we can actually
become numb to it.

00:03:26.270 --> 00:03:29.740 align:middle line:84%
As you watch this video
about where we are now,

00:03:29.740 --> 00:03:32.580 align:middle line:84%
I invite you to let
it all in deeply

00:03:32.580 --> 00:03:35.920 align:middle line:84%
and listen with your heart
as well as your mind.

00:03:35.920 --> 00:03:38.680 align:middle line:84%
Letting in the scope and impact
of our current global crisis

00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:42.270 align:middle line:84%
can be disturbing, and it takes
courage to face the reality

00:03:42.270 --> 00:03:44.160 align:middle line:90%
of our present situation.

00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:46.370 align:middle line:84%
But it's important
to let yourself feel

00:03:46.370 --> 00:03:48.600 align:middle line:84%
and not distance
yourself from it.

